;left:0;line-height:0;width:100%;font-size:65px;transition:transform 0.3s,opacity 0.3s}.chart:hover .fa{opacity:0;transform:scale(1.5)}.joomla{color:#e52626}.joomla .outer{stroke:#e52626}.css3{color:#1572b6}.css3 .outer{stroke:#1572b6}.html5{color:#e34f26}.html5 .outer{stroke:#e34f26}.email{color:#A2133C}.email .outer{stroke:#A2133C}.wordpress{color:#fff}.wordpress .outer{stroke:#fff}.drupal{color:#00598f}.drupal .outer{stroke:#00598f}.chart svg{position:absolute;top:0;left:0}.outer{fill:transparent;stroke:#333;stroke-width:20;stroke-dasharray:534;transition:stroke-dashoffset 1s;-webkit-animation-play-state:running;-moz-transform:rotate(-89deg) translateX(-190px)}.chart[data-percent='100'] .outer{stroke-dashoffset:0;-webkit-animation:show100 2s;animation:show100 2s}.chart[data-percent='95'] .outer{stroke-dashoffset:27;-webkit-animation:show95 2s;animation:show95 2s}.chart[data-percent='90'] .outer{stroke-dashoffset:54;-webkit-animation:show90 2s;animation:show90 2s}.chart[data-percent='80'] .outer{stroke-dashoffset:107;-webkit-animation:show80 2s;animation:show80 2s}.chart[data-percent='45'] .outer{stroke-dashoffset:294;-webkit-animation:show45 2s;animation:show45 2s}</style><noscript><style>img[data-jchll=true]{display:none}</style> </noscript> </head><body class=""> <header><div class=branding><h1>Hi.</h1><p>I'm Glenn!<br>I'm <span id=describe-before>a </span><span id=describe-me>front-end developer.</span> </p></div><nav><ul class=""> <li class=item101><a class=homelink href=/joomla/index.php><span data-hover=Home>Home</span></a></li><li class=item159><a class=About href=/joomla/index.php/about><span data-hover=About>About</span></a></li><li id=current class="selected item110"><a class=Proficiencies href=/joomla/index.php/proficiencies><span data-hover=Proficiencies>Proficiencies</span></a></li><li class=item111><a class=contactlink href=/joomla/index.php/contact><span data-hover=Contact>Contact</span></a></li></ul></nav> </header><section class=content-main><div class=content><div class="item-page "><p><div class="moduletable banner"><h2>My Proficiencies</h2><h4>So what am I good at anyway?</h4></div><div class="moduletable proficiencies-radial"><figure class="chart joomla" data-percent=100><figcaption>Joomla</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-joomla"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure><figure class="chart css3" data-percent=95><figcaption>CSS3</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-css3"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure><figure class="chart html5" data-percent=95><figcaption>HTML5</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-html5"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure><figure class="chart email" data-percent=90><figcaption>EDMs</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-envelope"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure><figure class="chart wordpress" data-percent=80><figcaption>WordPress</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-wordpress"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure><figure class="chart drupal" data-percent=45><figcaption>Drupal</figcaption> <em class="fa fa-drupal"></em> <svg width=200 height=200> <circle class=outer cx=95 cy=95 r=85 transform="rotate(-90, 95, 95)"></circle> </svg> </figure> </div> </p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>To sum up the above...</h4><ul> <li><strong>Joomla - 100%</strong>: Joomla's my jam...</li> <li><strong>CSS3 &amp; HTML5 - 95%</strong>: Got it down, but there's always an obscure new thing to surprise me.</li> <li><strong>Email templates / EDMs - 90%</strong>: Coding like it's 1999... It's always challenging, but I do well.</li> <li><strong>WordPress - 80%</strong>: Have done a lot of builds in WordPress, but I feel like there's still more to know.</li> <li><strong>Drupal - 45%</strong>: I've done work on Drupal sites in the past - there's plenty I can do, but plenty more I can learn.</li> </ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Anything Else?</h3><p><strong>Yes!</strong> The following list should cover it:</p><ul> <li><strong>Site Optimisation</strong>: I can get a little obsessed with this when left to my own devices... I have many tools in my tool belt for this...</li> <li><strong>PHP</strong>: I do well with PHP - most of what I do in a day is in PHP.</li> <li><strong>JavaScript / jQuery</strong>: Have done plenty with this - very comfortable with it.</li> <li><strong>Vision6 / MailChimp</strong>: I've done many email templates in these - they always turn out great.</li> <li><b>SQL</b>: Sometimes a CMS doesn't give you everything you need and you have to go straight to the database - I've had quite a bit of experience with this.</li> <li><strong>BigCommerce</strong>: Have had a couple of clients in this.</li> <li><strong>SquareSpace</strong>: Have had a couple of clients in this too.</li> <li>and I've dabbled a little with <strong>SVGs</strong></li> </ul> </div> </div> </section><footer><div class=container> <span>&copy; Glenn Domin 2017</span> </div></footer> <script>var cb=function(){var l=document.createElement('link');l.rel='stylesheet';l.href='/joomla/cache/plg_jch_optimize/22bbc146de62116c785f719441882cb9_0.css';var h=document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0];h.appendChild(l);};var raf=requestAnimationFrame||mozRequestAnimationFrame||webkitRequestAnimationFrame||msRequestAnimationFrame;if(raf)raf(cb);else window.addEventListener('load',cb);</script><noscript><link rel=stylesheet property=stylesheet href=/joomla/cache/plg_jch_optimize/22bbc146de62116c785f719441882cb9_0.css /></noscript> <script src=/joomla/cache/plg_jch_optimize/5b29e7795678ae8368e0a4e72df87581_0.js async></script> </body> </html>";s:13:"mime_encoding";s:9:"text/html";s:7:"headers";a:6:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"na